TCS NQT utilizes a single integrated adaptive test pattern where your performance 
dictates whether you qualify for the Ninja, Digital, or Prime job profile. 

THE PRIMARY CHALLENGE: You cannot switch back to previous questions once you hit 
'Next' (Question Locking). Time allocation and rapid topic-spotting are everything.
The Foundation Numerical Ability section typically features 20 to 26 questions 
to be solved in 40 minutes.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🟥 TIER 1: HIGHEST PRIORITY (Maximum Weightage & High ROI)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
These topics appear in the highest volumes (typically 2-3 questions each). 
Mastering these shortcuts allows you to comfortably crack them in under 45-60 seconds.

1. Data Interpretation
   - Subtopics: Tabular Data, Graphical Data, Pie Charts
   - Weightage: Very High (3-4 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy to Moderate (45 - 75 seconds)
   - TCS Internal Insight / Trap to Avoid: TCS provides massive, intimidating calculation 
     sets. Do not calculate exact values. Master percentage approximations and 
     option elimination to stay under 60 seconds.

2. Arithmetic: Percentages, Profit & Loss
   - Subtopics: Successive percentage change, Marked Price & Discounts
   - Weightage: High (2-3 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (30 - 50 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: Avoid using the traditional equation-based 'x' method. Use 
     fraction conversion (e.g., 20% = 1/5, 16.66% = 1/6) to solve mentally.

3. Work and Time
   - Subtopics: Mandays (M1*D1*H1/W1 = M2*D2*H2/W2), Individual Efficiencies, Pipes & Cisterns
   - Weightage: High (2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (40 - 50 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: Never use classic fraction additions (1/x + 1/y). Use the 
     Total Work LCM Method. It drops solve times down to 30 seconds.

4. Ratios and Proportion
   - Subtopics: Income/Expenditure ratios, Partnerships
   - Weightage: High (1-2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (30 - 45 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: Directly substitute the options into the ratio values. If a 
     ratio demands a multiple of 7, check the options for multiples of 7 first 
     before solving.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🟨 TIER 2: HIGH WEIGHTAGE BUT TIME-CONSUMING (The 60-Second Edge)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
These topics are guaranteed to show up, but they are conceptually heavier. With 
proper training, they can be tamed to fit our 60-second rule.

5. Number System
   - Subtopics: Divisibility Rules, Numbers and Decimal Fractions, HCF & LCM
   - Weightage: High (2-3 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (50 - 70 seconds)
   - TCS Internal Insight / Trap to Avoid: TCS likes huge numbers. Rely heavily on 
     unit digit analysis, last two digits, and divisibility constraints (especially 
     rules for 7, 11, 13, and 19) instead of complete long division.

6. Distance, Speed and Time
   - Subtopics: Trains crossing, Relative Speed, Average Speed
   - Weightage: Moderate to High (1-2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (60 - 80 seconds)
   - TCS Internal Insight / Trap to Avoid: Avoid unit conversion errors (km/hr to m/s). 
     Use the proportional method: If speed is constant, Distance is proportional to Time. 
     This stops you from writing messy equations.

7. Arithmetic: Averages & Ages
   - Subtopics: Weighted Averages, Age ratios over time
   - Weightage: Moderate (1-2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy to Moderate (40 - 60 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: For averages, use the deviation method from an assumed mean 
     rather than calculating the absolute sum of large numbers.

8. Allegations and Mixtures
   - Subtopics: Milk-water replacements, Weighted balance
   - Weightage: Moderate (1 Question)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (50 - 60 seconds)
   - The Strategy: This is a meta-topic. Master the cross-multiplication allegory 
     diagram because it can also be used to solve complex average and profit/loss 
     questions in under 40 seconds.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🟦 TIER 3: MODERATE WEIGHTAGE & FORMULA HEAVY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
These topics require explicit formulas. If you know the formula, they take 30 
seconds. If you forget it, you will lose precious time.

9. Elementary Statistics
   - Subtopics: Mean, Median, Mode, Standard Deviation and Variance
   - Weightage: Moderate (1-2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (30 - 50 seconds)
   - The Strategy: High ROI because the math is simple addition/division. Remember 
     the empirical formula: Mode = 3(Median) - 2(Mean).

10. Simplifications & Calculations
    - Subtopics: Simple Arithmetic Calculations, Approximations
    - Weightage: Moderate (1-2 Questions)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (40 - 60 seconds)
    - The Rules: Strictly enforce BODMAS/VBODMAS. TCS adds nested brackets to 
      test your nerve under pressure. Use digital scratchpads cleanly.

11. Mensuration & Geometry
    - Subtopics: Geometry, Shapes, Area & Perimeter, Volume
    - Weightage: Moderate (1 Question)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate to Hard (60 - 90 seconds)
    - The Strategy: Focus heavily on circles, cylinders, and spheres. If finding 
      an area/volume involves Pi, check if options are divisible by 11.

12. Series and Progressions
    - Subtopics: Arithmetic Progression (AP), Geometric Progression (GP)
    - Weightage: Moderate (1 Question)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (50 - 70 seconds)
    - The Trap: Trying to manually calculate terms. Memorize nth term formulas 
      and sum of series formulas to keep calculations programmatic.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
⬛ TIER 4: CONCEPTUAL & ADVANCED (Save for Last or Advanced Section)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Low question frequency in the Foundation tier, but heavily featured in the 
Advanced Quantitative section for Digital/Prime roles.

13. Permutations & Combinations
    - Subtopics: Arrangements, Selections
    - Weightage: Low (0-1 Question in Foundation)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Hard (70 - 90 seconds)
    - The Strategy: Focus purely on linear arrangements with constraints 
      (e.g., "vowels sitting together"). Avoid deeply complex grid problems.

14. Probability
    - Subtopics: Coin/Dice/Cards problems, Conditional Probability
    - Weightage: Low (0-1 Question in Foundation)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Hard (60 - 90 seconds)
    - The Concept: Usually asked in tandem with P&C. Focus heavily on standard 
      card decks and dice-rolling shortcuts.

15. Clocks and Calendar
    - Subtopics: Angle between hands, Odd days mapping
    - Weightage: Low (0-1 Question)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate to Hard (60 - 80 seconds)
    - The Shortcut: For clocks, use the standard formula for angle Theta:
      Theta = | 30*H - (11/2)*M |

16. Equations
    - Subtopics: Linear & Quadratic equations
    - Weightage: Low (0-1 Question)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (40 - 60 seconds)
    - The Shortcut: Never solve the quadratic equation manually. Use the sum of 
      roots (-b/a) and product of roots (c/a) or just back-substitute options.

